'''"Tiger" Tom Pistone''' (born March 17, 1929 in Chicago, Illinois, [[United States|USA]]) is a former [[NASCAR]] [[Sprint Cup Series|Grand National]] driver from Chicago.<ref name="RacingReference">{{cite web|url=http://racing-reference.info/driver/pistoto01|title=Driving statistics|publisher=Racing-Reference|accessdate=20 March 2010}}</ref> He made his Grand National debut in 1955.<ref name="RacingReference" /> He won two races and finished 6th in championship points in the 1959 season for [[Carl Rupert]], his best season statistically.<ref name="RacingReference" /> He was away from NASCAR in 1963 and 1964, but returned in 1965 to drive in 33 races for [[Glen Sweet]] and [[Emory Gilliam]], a career high, but only 8 top tens and a 32nd place points finish came of it.<ref name="RacingReference" /> His final and 130th cup race came in 1968.<ref name="RacingReference" /> He won two [[NASCAR Convertible Division]] races.<ref name="RacingReference" />

In 1960, he wore a life preserver and an oxygen tube in his car while racing at Daytona for fear of running into the lake in the middle of the speedway and drowning. This happened after [[Tommy Irwin (racing driver)|Tommy Irwin]] ran into the lake in the [[Gatorade Duels|first qualifying race]]. Irwin did not drown, however.<ref>Dykes, Dan. [http://racingthroughtime.com/ARCHIVES/OCT09/10-14-09.htm Yet Another Dose of Racin<U+2019> Remembrances], ''Racing Through Time'', Volume 1, Number 41, October 14, 2009, Retrieved 2010-03-20</ref>

On October 17, 2010, Pistone was one of the year's 15 inductees to the Racers' Reunion Hall of Fame, located at Memory Lane Museum in Mooresville NC.<ref>http://www.thatsracin.com/2010/11/23/52805/museum-works-to-preserve-racing.html#</ref>

Still active in racing at age 81, Pistone has a thriving race car parts business in Charlotte, NC, and can often be found mentoring young drivers at Charlotte Motor Speedway.  He prepares and crews for several Legends and Bandolero drivers in the Winter Heat and Summer Shootout series.<ref>www.pistonetigertom.com</ref>

In April 2011, Pistone appeared on an episode of The History Channel's [[American Pickers]] in which he sold items to be placed in the [[NASCAR Hall of Fame]].<ref>{{Cite episode |title=NASCAR Challenge |episodelink=http://www.history.com/shows/american-pickers/episodes/season-2 |series= |serieslink= |credits= |network=[[History (U.S. TV channel)|The History Channel]] |station= |airdate=2011-04-11 |season=2 |seriesno= |number= |minutes= |quote= |language=}}</ref>

